            <div type="edition">
            <ab>
                <lb n="1"/><persName><name key="Φαυλέας">Φαυλέας</name></persName> ἀνέθυσε τõι <persName type="divine"><name key="Πᾶν">Πανί</name></persName>.
                
                
                
                
            </ab></div>
            
            <div type="translation">
            <p>Phauleas dedicated (this) to Pan.</p></div>

            <div type="commentary">
            <p>A small dedicatory status with inscription on the base. The item is one of several
                    bronze figurines found in Andritzena in Southern Arcadia, dated to the sixth
                    century BCE. Pan was the patron god of shepherds, which suggests that the
                    dedicator Phauleas was a shepherd himself. The pileus, pointed hat, was worn by
                    travelers, and the stute could represent Phauleas. </p></div>
            
